The intersection curve of cylinders of axis Z and axis X or Y
is given by the longitude of its initial point and final point.
The longitude is the angle (Ox,OM), in degrees
often written TETA as cylindar coordinates
   0 =< TETA =< 360 degrees 
                  
Al0caz  is the initial longitude followed by
Al1caz     the final longitude

EXAMPLE:  0;  90;   means the sector X>0 Y>0
         90; 180;   means the sector X<0 Y>0 ...
